In this press briefing, Press Secretary Jay Carney discusses the government shutdown and the debt ceiling. He emphasizes that the President is concerned about the possibility of Republicans using the same tactics they used to shut down the government to also threaten defaulting on the debt ceiling. Carney explains that the President is urging Republicans to do the right thing and open the government without any partisan demands. He mentions that there are many Republicans who would vote to reopen the government if given the opportunity. Carney also discusses the President's upcoming trip to Asia and the importance of US engagement in the region. He addresses concerns about the impact of defaulting on the debt ceiling and emphasizes the serious consequences it would have on the economy and the American people. Carney states that the President is not willing to negotiate over the debt ceiling and that he believes Congress needs to fulfill its responsibility to raise the debt ceiling and ensure that the United States pays its bills.